race.comment: MAGIC ANDERSON (5) made an encouraging debut last time out, finishing 2.5 lengths from the winner in third over 1000m at Queanbeyan. Sharp improver who goes close. ZOU ROYAL (10) made an encouraging debut last time out, finishing 5.5 lengths from the winner in fifth over 1000m at Wyong. Leading player with plenty of improvement in store. BOLD ROSIE (6) was sixth on debut, then ran third last time out over 1100m at Narromine. Well in with the claim from the low draw. Respect. LUCKY MONKEY (8) has been racing in stronger company than this recently and drops way back in grade today. Not to be discounted.
